race.comment: BATTLE WARRIOR (8) returned from a let-up with a fading fourth over 1100m here on the heavy (9) surface. Molly Bourke stays on and strips fitter now. Each way contender from the sticky gate. CUBAN RAIN (3) gets a better set-up for this from the inside gate and will relish the drop in class. No match for the smart Aisle Two with a plugging seventh over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Tongue-tie comes off and capable of taking this out. BRAVE XENA (9) slick debut winner over this course and distance on the heavy (9) track. Has the upside to test some of these. Worth thought. MISS MIKKI ISLE (7) is better than she showed last start at the Sapphire Coast and can bounce back today with the blinkers on.
